<h2>Chapter 7: Turning Followers Into Customers</h2>
<p>Followers are not customers. You need a system to convert attention into revenue. Here is how local businesses turn Instagram engagement into bookings, calls, and store visits.</p>
<h3>DM Response Speed</h3>
<p>72% of customers expect a response within 1 hour on social media. For local businesses, DM response speed directly correlates with conversion rate. A lead who messages you about a service and gets a reply in 10 minutes is far more likely to book than one who waits 24 hours.</p>
<p>Set up Quick Reply templates for your most common DM questions. Instagram allows up to 20 saved replies. Create templates for pricing inquiries, availability, and directions.</p>
<p>Turn on notifications for DMs. If you cannot monitor Instagram all day, check DMs 3 times: morning, lunch, and evening.</p>
<h3>Link in Bio Optimization</h3>
<p>Your link in bio is the bridge between Instagram and revenue. Track which posts drive the most profile visits using Instagram Insights. Then make sure the link in bio matches whatever you are promoting.</p>
<p>If you post a Reel about kitchen remodels, your link should go to your kitchen remodel page or a quote request form. Not your generic homepage. Update the link when you change your content focus.</p>
<h3>Instagram Stories With Link Stickers</h3>
<p>Every business account can add link stickers to Stories. Use them to send viewers directly to your booking page, a specific service page, or a special offer. Add a clear call to action on the Story itself. "Tap the link to book" works better than just dropping a link with no context.</p>
<h3>Converting DMs Into Bookings</h3>
<p>When someone messages you, follow this process:</p>
<ol>
<li>Reply within 1 hour (or faster)</li>
<li>Answer their question directly</li>
<li>Ask 1 qualifying question ("What area are you in?" or "When do you need this done?")</li>
<li>Send a link to book or get a quote</li>
<li>Follow up within 24 hours if they do not respond</li>
</ol>
<p>This is not aggressive sales. It is good customer service. Most local businesses lose leads simply by responding too slowly or not at all.</p>
<h2>Chapter 8: Instagram Ads for Local Businesses</h2>
<p>Organic reach is powerful, but Instagram Ads let you target exact locations with exact budgets. You do not need thousands of dollars. Many local businesses see results with $5-15 per day.</p>
<h3>Boost Your Top-Performing Posts</h3>
<p>The easiest way to start with Instagram Ads is boosting. Find your best-performing organic post (the one with the most saves, shares, or comments). Tap "Boost Post" and set your target location to your service area.</p>
<p>This works because the content is already proven. The algorithm already showed it to your followers and they engaged with it. Now you are paying to show it to more people in your area.</p>
<h3>Location Targeting</h3>
<p>Instagram Ads let you target by city, zip code, or a radius around your business. For most local businesses, a 10-25 mile radius works well. Tighten it to 5-10 miles for businesses with a physical location where customers visit in person.</p>
<p>Layer location targeting with interest targeting. A gym in Austin can target people within 10 miles who are interested in "fitness," "weight loss," or "personal training."</p>
