<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3>How often should a local business post on Instagram?</h3>
<p>3-4 posts per week is the sweet spot for most local businesses. This includes a mix of Reels, carousels, photos, and Stories. Consistency matters more than frequency. Posting 3 times per week every week outperforms posting 7 times 1 week and then nothing for 2 weeks.</p>
<h3>Do hashtags still work on Instagram in 2026?</h3>
<p>Yes. Hashtags help your content appear in search results and on the Explore page. Use 5-15 hashtags per post with a mix of local, industry, and niche tags. Avoid using 30 hashtags or spamming irrelevant tags, as this can reduce your reach.</p>
<h3>Is Instagram better than Facebook for local businesses?</h3>
<p>Instagram delivers higher engagement rates per post and reaches a younger demographic (18-44). Facebook has a larger total user base and better options for community groups. Most local businesses benefit from using both, but Instagram gives more organic reach per post with less effort.</p>
<h3>How much should a local business spend on Instagram Ads?</h3>
<p>Start with $150-300 per month by boosting your best-performing organic posts. Target a 10-25 mile radius around your business. You can scale up once you see which posts and audiences convert. Many local businesses see positive ROI at $10-15 per day.</p>
<h3>What type of Instagram content works best for local businesses?</h3>
<p>Reels get the most reach (3-5x more than static posts). Carousels get the most saves. Stories keep you visible daily. The best strategy combines all 3 formats. Focus 40% of your content on showcasing your work and behind-the-scenes moments, 25% on educational tips, 20% on social proof, and 15% on promotions.</p>
<h3>Can Instagram replace a website for a local business?</h3>
<p>No. Instagram is a discovery and engagement platform, not a replacement for a website. You do not own your Instagram audience. The algorithm can change, and your reach can drop overnight. Use Instagram to drive traffic to your website, where you control the experience and capture leads directly.</p>
